.TH man 1 "10th December"  "0.1" "man_simple_shell page"

.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- A C-based simple shell designed for interaction with a Linux operating system.

.SH SYNOPSIS
./hsh [options] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple_Shell is an sh-compatible command language interpreter that executes
commands read from the standard input.

.SH Return Value

Returns 0 on success; other numbers indicate failure.

.SH PATH

Searches within all directories specified in the PATH environment variable for executables.

.SH OPTIONS
.B simple_shell
Commands options are entered after the main command, separated by a space and a
'-' symbol.

.SH EXAMPLE

[command] [options]
$ ls -l

.SH SEE ALSO
.I peerlearning(2), fullstack(2), projectbased(2), Betty(1)

.SH BUGS
A single space is required after arguments.

.SH AUTHOR
KENEETH KARIUKI
